      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARAKI (5) started at $9.80 last time on the back of a win at this track two starts ago but was below his best, finishing eighth over 1000m at this track. Gustavo Adrian Aros gets the best out of this six-year-old gelding. Suitably placed so anticipating a big run this time. COKE SPIRIT (2) last appeared a week-and-a-half ago over 1000m at this track when he finished ninth. This is his first run for the Gonzalez Morales Juan stable. Worth serious consideration. LADY IN BLACK (8) improved last time out, finishing 3 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 1300m at this track. Has her share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. HUASO DERREPENTE (6) has been about the mark of late. Last time out was 0.3 lengths from the winner in second over 1000m at this track. Has good early speed so should take up a forward position. Don't underestimate.",
